author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: The government has dismissed as false social media claims of explosions in Udhampur and drone sightings in Jammu and Kashmir, urging the public to trust only official sources. The rumours surfaced amid India-Pakistan tensions following the April 22 Pahalgam terror attack, which killed 26 people. India retaliated with strikes on terror camps; both nations have now agreed to a ceasefire.

description: A devastating road accident on the Raipur-Baloda Bazar highway claimed the lives of at least 13 people, including women and children, as a goods vehicle carrying passengers collided head-on with a speeding trailer truck. description: Donald Trump defended accepting a luxury jet from Qatar for Air Force One, calling it a free gift and accusing Democrats of outrage over a cost-saving deal. description: A recent study reveals that even brief exposure to junk food advertising significantly increases children's calorie consumption, regardless of whether the ads feature actual food. Addressing this requires a multi-faceted approach involving parents, schools, and policymakers to promote healthier lifestyles.
title: Just 5 minutes of junk food ads can drive kids to eat more: Study
